								First Peach Ale™							










Tweet #TwitterStories




LOCATE THIS BEER







History


Profile


Food Pairing






First Peach Ale

	With one foot in winter and the other in spring, we crafted this Belgian-inspired Brown Ale with the first peaches of the season and coriander. It has a tart taste balanced by caramel malts for the cooler days and peach notes for the warmer ones.


	Available from January through March.





Ingredients and Profile

Malts: Imported Caramel Malt and Wheat  Hops: Mittelfruh   Our Twist: A classic Belgian sour brown ale with an American Peach Wheat Ale  IBUs: 15   Original Gravity: 13.9° Plato  ABV: 5.6%  

Appearance
																Clear, deep amber-colored ale with an off-white head.															

Aroma
																Assertive, peach aroma with a hint of caramel malt.															

Taste
																Notable natural peach taste with a light caramel malt sweetness and mild tartness.															

Mouthfeel
																Medium body with hint of dryness.															

Finish
																Light peach flavor with mild tartness and slight sweetness.															




Food Pairing
The natural, tart, peach taste of this beer will bring out the flavors of nutty dishes, and creamy desserts combined with peach, like peach pie. 



















